: Running Code Without Servers Using AWS Lambda
Step 1: Access AWS Lambda
Log in to AWS Management Console

Visit the AWS Management Console.
Enter your AWS credentials to log in.
Navigate to AWS Lambda

In the AWS Management Console, search for “AWS Lambda” and select it.
Step 2: Create a New Function
Start Function Creation

Click on “Create function.”
Configure Function Settings

Choose “Author from scratch.”
Enter a name for your function.
Select a runtime (e.g., Python, Node.js).
Choose or create an IAM role for your function.
Write and Deploy Code

Input your code directly in the console or upload it as a ZIP file.
Set Up Triggers

Configure triggers and event sources as needed (e.g., API Gateway, S3 bucket).
Step 3: Test Your Function
Use the Test Feature
Test your function using the built-in testing feature to ensure it operates correctly.
Free Tier Limit: 1 million requests and 400,000 GB-seconds of compute time per month.

